# GitHub Actions

## Workflow (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`)

| Job | Steps |
|-----|-------|
| `api` | `dotnet restore/build/test` on `Template.sln` / `apps/api.tests` |
| `web` | `npm ci`, `type-check`, `lint`, `test:unit --run`, `build` in `apps/web` |
| `e2e` | needs api+web; Playwright in `e2e/` with `CI=true` |

## Versions

- .NET: `9.0.x`
- Node: `22` (cache `apps/web/package-lock.json`)

## Local parity

Use skill `run-ci-locally` to reproduce failures before pushing.

```yaml
# ✅ GOOD — working-directory for web job
defaults:
  run:
    working-directory: apps/web
```

## Do not

- Reference `frontend/` or `backend/Api/` paths
- Skip `npm run type-check` or `lint` in web job
- Run e2e before api/web jobs succeed

Fix failures with skill `fix-ci-failure`.
